<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE topic PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN" "topic.dtd">
<topic id="reusables-sdk-webauthor">
  <title>Reusable Components for both Web Author/WA Customization</title>
  <body>
    <!--framework customization-->
    <p product="webauthor waCustom">
      <ol id="upload-framework-ol">
        <li>Go to your <xref href="../../topics/webapp-admin-page.dita#webapp-admin-page"
            >Administration Page</xref>.</li>
        <li>Select <uicontrol>Frameworks</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li>
          <p>Click <uicontrol>Upload Framework</uicontrol> and choose a <term>framework</term> to
              upload.<note type="important">The framework should be a ZIP or JAR archive that
              contains exactly one folder. This folder should contain the framework descriptor file
              with the <filepath>.framework</filepath> extension and other supporting files. If the
              uploaded archive does not have this format you will receive an error that the upload
              was rejected.</note></p>
          <p><b>Step Result:</b> The <term>framework</term> should appear in the list on this
              <uicontrol>Frameworks</uicontrol> page. Uploaded frameworks appear with a light green
            highlight so that you can identify them easily.</p>
        </li>
        <li>Once you are finished with all of your changes, restart the server.</li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </body>
</topic>
